# MapTour вҖ” System Architecture

**Date**: 2026-03-28
**Status**: Draft
**Spec**: speckit.specify

---

## Summary

MapTour is a client-side JavaScript library distributed as a single bundle. It reads a YAML tour file, renders a Leaflet map and stop card UI, tracks GPS position, and provides navigation deep-links. There is no server component. All state is in-browser (DOM + localStorage).

---

## Technical Context

**Language**: JavaScript (ES2022), TypeScript for source
**Build tool**: Vite вҖ” produces a single IIFE bundle (`maptour.js`) and one stylesheet (`maptour.css`)
**Primary dependencies**:
- `leaflet` ~1.9 вҖ” map rendering
- `js-yaml` вҖ” YAML parsing
- `vitest` вҖ” unit tests
- `playwright` вҖ” E2E tests
- `axe-core` вҖ” WCAG audit in CI

**Storage**: localStorage only (visited stops, nav app preference)
**Testing**: Vitest (unit), Playwright (E2E against a local static server)
**Target platform**: Modern browsers (Chrome/Firefox/Safari, вүӨ3 years old), desktop and mobile
**Project type**: Embeddable JS library
**Performance goals**: Initial load <3 s on 4G mobile; bundle <200 KB gzipped
**Constraints**: No server, no build step for end-user, no global CSS side-effects
**Scale/scope**: Single-page player, tours of 5вҖ“100 stops

---

